        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(telegram): consume trailing notify=false marker and send silent",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nWhen agents append a trailing standalone `notify=false` to request silent delivery, the marker leaks into the visible Telegram message body instead of being applied as delivery metadata.\n\n## Root Cause\n\nThe marker was not consumed before text entered Telegram delivery paths. Each path (media, native reply, sendMessage) would need individual handling, leaving gaps.\n\n## Fix\n\nConsume the marker once in `sendTelegramPayloadMessages` — the **shared upstream entry point** for ALL Telegram outbound paths. This single fix covers media fan-out, native reply delivery, and text sendMessage.\n\n- 1 file, 18 lines\n- Marker stripped from visible text\n- Sets `silent: true` which maps to `disable_notification=true`\n- Inline mentions of `notify=false` are preserved\n\nCloses #80569\n\n## Change Type\n\n- [x] Bug fix\n\n## Scope\n\n- [x] Telegram channel (outbound adapter)\n\n## Evidence\n\n### All delivery paths covered\n\n| Path | Covered by |\n|------|-----------|\n| sendMessage | ✅ shared entry point |\n| Media fan-out | ✅ shared entry point |\n| Native reply | ✅ shared entry point |\n\n### Test suite\n\n```\n$ npx vitest run extensions/telegram/src/outbound-adapter.test.ts\nTest Files  1 passed (1)\nTests       27 passed (27)\n\n$ npx vitest run extensions/telegram/src/send.test.ts\nTest Files  1 passed (1)\nTests       139 passed (139)\n```\n\n### Marker parsing proof\n\n```\n✅ trailing standalone → \"text\"\n✅ marker only → \"\"\n✅ whitespace around marker → \"\"\n✅ inline — skipped\n✅ not at end — skipped\n✅ no marker\n6/6 passed\n```\n\n### Formatting\n\n```\n$ pnpm exec oxfmt --check extensions/telegram/src/outbound-adapter.ts\nAll matched files use the correct format.\n```\n\n## Security Impact\n\n- New permissions? No\n- Secrets handling changed? No\n- New network calls? No",
